Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Portrait"

- Photocopies of some pages of "De iconografie van de Contra-Reformatic in de Nederlanden", 1939
- Essay (reprint): 'Recente aanwinsten van het Rubenshuis - I', in "Tijdschrift der Stad Antwerpen", April 1965
- Brochure of "Jahrbuch der Staatlichen Kunstsammlungen in Baden-Württemberg"
- Notes about different portraits
- Extracts from different publications
- Reproduction of 'Francesco IV, Duke of Mantua' portrait
- Correspondence with Wolfgang J. Müller (dated 1964), with Maria Sczesny (dated 1960), with Bruno Lohse (dated 1967), with Rolf Linnenkamp (dated 1968), with W. Schommer (dated 1968) and with Madame Guillibert de la Lauzière
- Small subfolder (Annotation: "Kardinal-Infant Ferdinand")
    - Bibliographic references
    - Notes about the 'Cardinal-Infante Ferdinand' portrait
    - Correspondence with Curt Reinheldt dated 1956
    - Booklet: "Das Porträt des Kardinalinfanten von Spanien Ferdinand von Österreich von A. van Dyck" by Curt Reinheldt  
  
Loose documentation reunited with the folder:  
    
- Reproduction of a portrait (Olivares ?)
